{
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "### ice_thickness",
        "",
        "This IDL notebook tests the functionality of the ice thickness calculation procedure.",
        "",
        "The procedure calculates the ice thickness per time step on the basis of the continuity equation, which is solved using a semi-implicit forward scheme.",
        "",
        "The continuity equation is given by:",
        "",
        "$$ \\frac{\\partial H}{\\partial t} = \\nabla \\cdot f + b $$",
        "",
        "Where:",
        "- $\\nabla \\cdot f$ is the local divergence of the ice flux",
        "- and $b$ is the surface mass balance",
        "",
        "Example calculations are performed for the Great Aletsch Glacier.",
        "",
        "Code authored by: Janosch Beer.",
        ""
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        ".compile load_glacier"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "text/plain",
              "content": [
                "% Compiled module: LOAD_GLACIER."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "id": "not-saved"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; define necessary parameters",
        "aflow = 1e-16            ; X = value of deformation-sliding factor (10^-16 Pa^-3 a^-1)",
        "dt_flag = 0              ; 0 = adaptive time step (dynamic); X = time step in years",
        "width_flag = 2           ; 0 = same width along the flowline (never used, may even not work anymore; was used for initial tests); 1 = rectangle transect (only used for sensitivity tests in paper); 2 = trapezium transect (classic)",
        "display_during_flag = 0  ; 0 = do not display anything during run (geometry and smb stuff); 1 = display during run --> may be useful for debugging/checks (is normally not used)",
        "dtfactor = 1             ; X = multiply dt by a certain factor --> can be used to avoid numerical instability",
        "start_year = 0           ; X = year in which the simulation starts (typically 0 for steady state experiments, and real year (e.g. 1950/1990) for transient simulations)",
        "flag_startobs = 2        ; 0 = start from zero ice thickness; 1 = start from observed geometry (at RGI inventory date); 2 = start from modelled geometry",
        "nyears = 5000            ; X = number of years for simulation (will stop earlier if steady state is reached, if numerical instability occurred, if ice is leaving the domain, or if there is no ice)"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; load glacier data",
        "result = load_glacier('01450', 'centraleurope', 0, 1.0/4.0, 0)",
        "dx = result.dx",
        "sur_input = result.sur_input",
        "th_input = result.th_input",
        "width_input = result.width_input",
        "length_fixeddistance = result.length_fixeddistance",
        "x_input = result.x_input"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "text/plain",
              "content": [
                "dx =          202",
                "volume_Huss_1d =    1.2761819e+10",
                "volume_Huss_1d_fixeddistance =    1.2907665e+10",
                "area_Huss_1d =        82165000.",
                "area_Huss_1d_fixeddistance =        82722555.",
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "id": "not-saved"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; load necessary variables",
        "@constants_counters_initialvalues_sizevariables ; constants, counters, initial values, size of variables",
        "@initial_geometry                               ; initial geometry (trapezoidal transect)"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "text/plain",
              "content": [
                "obs_vol_flowlinemodel =   1.29400e+10",
                "obs_vol_trapezium =   1.29400e+10",
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "id": "not-saved"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; calculate the diffusivity",
        "@diffusivity"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "df"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "text/plain",
              "content": [
                "       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000",
                "       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000",
                "       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000",
                "       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000",
                "       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000       0.0000000",
                "       1279.3633       10249.444       17041.678       18089.566       15734.298",
                "       19584.736       23809.818       37326.824       35303.832       5114.6133",
                "       6525.6968       2104.4165       98270.078       320424.50       456298.44",
                "       276483.50       91402.836       56321.723       300674.59       918626.62",
                "       914031.81       266715.38       138933.08       140935.02       215863.86",
                "       201352.55       133236.88       71929.062       18477.703       803.96051",
                "       4293.9849       2452.3293       8442.8916       39870.816       347103.69",
                "       767476.75       651203.94       46381.414       237953.92       1489498.6",
                "       101727.02       1664339.0       3734954.5       3071862.0       1082028.4",
                "       712696.12       532406.75       246233.27       59940.848       76019.695",
                "       560903.75       913474.75       649088.75       125201.36       1797.3418",
                "       19591.170       206659.19       857897.31       4825016.5       5321423.0",
                "       2490139.0       1569121.4       583460.38       318898.84       255651.22",
                "       156375.95       86082.883       54918.871       47993.957       57858.820",
                "       72991.812       79635.352       77280.438       64596.473       57990.879",
                "       63800.555       65739.375       50705.438       42661.430       43450.406",
                "       43508.656       28072.713       15231.942       12920.558       12685.066",
                "       22388.010       35121.836       47640.902       36675.859       19357.342",
                "       15144.441       11937.785       11446.534       9743.3730       7172.1421",
                "       4054.3728       1534.2584       148.24588       0.0000000"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "id": "not-saved"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "for j = 0, 2 do begin ; 3 sub-steps used. Worked well. Maybe not really needed or better solutions --> will have to be tested for other regions in the world",
        "",
        "    ; ; Define unstaggered grid for flux (fun)",
        "    fun = fltarr(xnum) ; Flux on unstaggered grid",
        "    for i = 2, xnum - 1 do begin",
        "      fun[i] = ((df[i - 1] + df[i]) / 2.0) * ((sur[i] - sur[i - 1]) / dx)",
        "    endfor",
        "  ",
        "    ; ; Calculate new ice thickness",
        "    for i = 1, xnum - 2 do begin",
        "      fluxdiv[i] = ((fun[i + 1] - fun[i]) / dx)",
        "      grad[i] = ((sur[i + 1] - sur[i - 1]) / (2 * dx)) ; surface gradient",
        "      term1[i] = fluxdiv[i] * width_mid[i]",
        "      term2[i] = ((width_mid[i + 1] - width_mid[i - 1]) / (2 * dx)) * grad[i] * df[i]",
        "      term3[i] = (term1[i] + term2[i]) / width_surface[i]",
        "      if ~finite(term3[i]) then term3[i] = 0 ; to avoid problems when width_surface == 0",
        "      th[i] = th[i] + (1.0 / 3.0) * dt * (term3[i] + bal[i])",
        "    endfor",
        "  ",
        "    i = where(th lt 0, count)",
        "    if count gt 0 then th[i] = 0 ; Faster than using 'if' statement in loop",
        "    th[xnum - 1] = th[xnum - 2] ; Thickness at last grid cell equals the thickness at penultimate grid cell",
        "  ",
        "    ; Call the script to renew various variables at these sub time-steps (surface elevation, width_mid and width_surface)",
        "    @variables_renew",
        "  endfor"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "w1 = window(dimensions = [800, 600])",
        "p1 = plot(indgen(n_elements(fluxdiv)), fluxdiv, /current, $",
        "    title = 'Flux Divergence', $",
        "    xtitle = 'Grid Index', ytitle = 'Flux Divergence (m²/year)', $",
        "    xrange = [0, n_elements(fluxdiv) - 1], $",
        "    color = 'blue', thick = 3.0)",
        "",
        "; Take the square root of fluxdiv",
        "; Check where fluxdiv is positive and negative",
        "positive_idx = where(fluxdiv ge 0, positive_count)",
        "negative_idx = where(fluxdiv lt 0, negative_count)",
        "",
        "; Compute the square root of the absolute value",
        "fluxdiv_sqrt = sqrt(abs(fluxdiv))",
        "",
        "; Adjust the sign based on the original fluxdiv values",
        "if positive_count gt 0 then fluxdiv_sqrt[positive_idx] *= 1",
        "if negative_count gt 0 then fluxdiv_sqrt[negative_idx] *= -1",
        "",
        "w2 = window(dimensions = [800, 600])",
        "",
        "; Plot the square root of fluxdiv",
        "p1_sqrt = plot(indgen(n_elements(fluxdiv_sqrt)), fluxdiv_sqrt, /current, $",
        "    title = 'Square Root of Flux Divergence', $",
        "    xtitle = 'Grid Index', ytitle = 'Flux Divergence (m/year)', $",
        "    xrange = [0, n_elements(fluxdiv_sqrt) - 1], $",
        "    color = 'magenta', thick = 3.0)"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "mime": "idl/notebook-renderer",
              "content": "{\"type\":\"idlnotebookimage_png\",\"item\":{\"xsize\":800,\"ysize\":600,\"data\":\"\"}}"
